Pour the boiled water from a full #kettle{} into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat. Add the @Basmati rice{150%g} and cook for ~{10-12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the saucepan. Cover with a #lid{} and leave to the side until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into small chunks. Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{40%g}. Drain and rinse the @mixed beans{1} in a sieve.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large saucepan on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the pepper and cook, stirring, for ~{3%minutes}.

Add the @Cajun spice mix{1} and @Worcester sauce{7.5%ml} to the pan. Cook for ~{30%seconds}. Stir in the @vegetable stock paste{10%ml}, @tomatoes with onion and garlic{1}(finely chopped), @sugar{1/2} and mixed beans. Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pop the @soured cream{75%g} into a #small bowl{}. Add a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Mix well.

Stir the @baby spinach{100%g} into the stew a handful at a time until wilted and piping hot, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{}, then share between your #bowls{}. Top with the veggie stew, a dollop of soured cream and a sprinkling of cheese. Enjoy!